#import "/formatting.typ": *
= Spicy Hummus <spicy-hummus>

== Equipment

- Food processor#Fn.food-processor
- Refrigerator

== Ingredients

// TODO: metric
- 1/4 cup tahini
- 27 g. (2 tbsp.) olive oil
- 1 tbsp. lemon juice
- 1 tbsp. minced garlic
- 1/2 tsp. ground cumin#Fn.cumin
- 1/2 tsp. salt
- 1/4 tsp. sesame oil
- As much spicy pepper as you can handle#footnote[~Habaneros & ghost peppers
  work great here. Fun for the whole family. Maybe not the whole family. Fun all
  the same.]
- 425 g. (15 oz.) garbanzo beans, cooked
- 30 to 60 g. (2 to 4 tbsp.) cold water#footnote[~More water #sym.arrow.r.double fluffier hummus.]

== Steps

+ Set aside garbanzos & water, and blend all other ingredients until smooth.
+ Add garbanzos; continue blending.
+ Add water; continue blending.
+ Chill hummus in refrigerator.
